{"questionId":"32940097","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The dog food is sold in closed cylindrical containers, with radius <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math> and height <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi></math>.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/5c5bd7ac1c1dc43ad9876053818b1531174865c0.png\"></p>\n<p>The whole container is made from one type of material, and it is assumed that the thickness of the material is negligible.</p>\n<p>Each container has a volume of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>400</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mi>cm</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Hence, find the area of the shaded region.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>15</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>15</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4166</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfrac><mn>185</mn><mn>12</mn></mfrac><mo>)</mo></math> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><msup><mi>cm</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>)</mo></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A2</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong><em><strong>: </strong></em>If their limits are outside the domain, award at most <em><strong>A1A0FT</strong></em>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"32940097","referenceCode":"24N.2.SL.TZ1.4bii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Hence, find the area of the shaded region.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.5—Integration introduction, areas between curve and x axis"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}
